The call uses the return value of MHD_socket_strerr_(err) as a read‑only format argument. If MHD_socket_strerr_ is declared to return 'char *' (i.e. a non‑const pointer) while it actually returns a pointer to an immutable error string (or otherwise is not intended to be modified), that declaration violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. The correct design is for MHD_socket_strerr_ to return 'const char *' so the pointer points to a const‑qualified type.
